%I A395791 #10 May 06 2026 16:15:11
%S A395791 10,14,18,21,22,26,28,30,33,34,38,39,42,44,46,50,51,52,54,55,56,57,58,
%T A395791 62,65,66,68,69,70,74,75,76,78,82,84,85,86,87,88,90,92,93,94,95,98,99,
%U A395791 100,102,104,105,106,108,110,111,114,115,116,117,118,119,122,123,124
%N A395791 Numbers k such that gcd(i!,k) = gcd((i-1)!,k) for some i <= A002034(k) not coprime to k.
%C A395791 If gcd(i!,k) > gcd((i-1)!,k), then clearly we have gcd(i,k) > 1 and that k does not divide (i-1)!. Sequence gives k such that the converse does not hold.
%C A395791 If k is squarefree, then k is a term if and only if (largest prime factor of k)/(smallest prime factor of k) > 2.
%H A395791 Jianing Song, <a href="/A395791/b395791.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10001</a>
%e A395791 10 is not a term since gcd(4!,10) = gcd(3!,10) = 2, and 4 is not coprime to 10.
%e A395791 1215 is not a term since gcd(10!,1215) = gcd(9!,1215) = 405, and 10 is not coprime to 1215.
%o A395791 (PARI) \\ See A395790.
%Y A395791 Cf. A002034. Complement of A395790.
